  "original_title": "\u2018\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da9\u0dca 19\u2019 \u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0ddc\u0dc5\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The damage to the brain caused by the 'Covid-19' virus is long-term",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Medical researchers at Oxford University in Britain say that the damage to the brain caused by the 'Covid 19' virus is long-term.",
        "The Oxford researchers further explain that brain damage emerges a year or two after being infected with the 'Covid-19' virus.",
        "Oxford researchers have discovered this after a study involving 1.25 million patients infected with 'Covid 19' in many European countries.",
        "Medical researchers explain that due to the damage to the brain, unconsciousness, dementia etc. are seen in patients who have recovered from 'Covid 19'."
      ],
